radiographic_examinations.findings: Small bilateral pleural effusions with adjacent consolidation, likely atelectasis; mild intrahepatic biliary duct dilation; tiny hypodensities in segment 6; small amount of fluid in the gallbladder fossa; normal pancreas; symmetric and normal kidneys; multiple hypodensities in the right kidney; moderate amount of intermediate density fluid within the pelvis; prominent mesenteric lymph nodes; no focal lytic or sclerotic osseous lesions; soft tissue stranding compatible with port site placement.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Tiny hypodensities in segment 6 are unchanged compared to prior CT.
